      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img&#xA;        class=&#34;lazyload&#34;&#xA;        src=&#34;https://www.theexpattech.com/svg/loading.min.svg&#34;&#xA;        data-src=&#34;https://www.theexpattech.com/living-in-mexico/qualifying-for-legal-residency-in-mexico/card.jpg&#34;&#xA;        data-srcset=&#34;https://www.theexpattech.com/living-in-mexico/qualifying-for-legal-residency-in-mexico/card.jpg, https://www.theexpattech.com/living-in-mexico/qualifying-for-legal-residency-in-mexico/card.jpg 1.5x, https://www.theexpattech.com/living-in-mexico/qualifying-for-legal-residency-in-mexico/card.jpg 2x&#34;&#xA;        data-sizes=&#34;auto&#34;&#xA;        alt=&#34;/living-in-mexico/qualifying-for-legal-residency-in-mexico/card.jpg&#34;&#xA;        title=&#34;image 1&#34; width=&#34;522&#34; height=&#34;314&#34; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;So you want to become a resident of Mexico but don&amp;rsquo;t know where to start?  Well, it isn&amp;rsquo;t as easy as just moving to Mexico and you are a resident.  You have to follow specific steps to become one.  If you are thinking of just getting a FMM (AKA Tourist Visa) and live in Mexico on it, those days are rapidly coming to an end.  INM (Mexican Immigration) has now networked their systems so that they can see who is trying to game the system and live in Mexico without follow the legal process.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
